Brutus is expecting a letter from you. The news Puteoli, Ι brought him about Accius’ Tereus was no news. July 9, n.c. He thought it was the Brutus} There had, however, 44 been some breath of rumour that at the opening of the Greek games the audience was small, at which, indeed, Ι was not at all surprised; for you know what Ι think of Greek games.

Now hear the most important point of all. Quintus has been with me several days, and, if I had desired‚ he would have stayed longer; but, so far as his visit went, you would not believe how pleased l was with him in every way, and especially in that in which l used most to disapprove of him. For he is so totally changed, partly by some works of mine, which I have in hand, and partly by my continual advice and exhortation, that he will in the future be as loyal as we could wish to the constitution.
